The paper deals with routing games, which are a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also discusses algorithms and optimization for network improvement, which falls under the category of network economics (cs.NE). The use of graphs and topology in the analysis suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents approximation algorithms, which are often studied in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
